<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-20T12:19:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-20T12:19:00-05:00" n="428" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 818.00/275</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Extract]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-20T12:00:00-05:19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1917,
                                noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Secretary of Government and Justice informs me Alfredo and José Volio,
                            Colonel Ricardo Monge, José Arias, Abel Robles and four others under the
                            leadership of M. Castro Quesada arrived all well armed and without
                            passports at Cote on Golfo Dulce and were taken under arrest to David
                            where they were released by his orders. He says that they wish to go to
                            Nicaragua and that if they have any intention of overthrowing Tinoco he
                            feels sure that they will do nothing from Panaman territory.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>